nodes.label: Autoimmune antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against the organism's own cells or tissues.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration or activity
nodes.def: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating protein concentration
nodes.def: An abnormal level of a circulating protein in the blood.

nodes.label: Spatial pattern
nodes.def: The pattern by which a phenotype affects one or more regions of the body.

nodes.label: Abnormal tissue enzyme concentration or activity
nodes.def: Concentration of an enyzme in a tissue is above or between the limit of normal. This term is intended to be used for enzymes that can be measured in multiple tissues other than blood.

nodes.label: Abnormal urine metabolite level
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal amount of a metabolite in urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal skeletal muscle morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

nodes.label: Abnormal CSF metabolite concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal range of concentration of a metabolite in the cerebrospinal fluid.

nodes.label: Pain
nodes.def: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.

nodes.label: Localized skin lesion
nodes.def: A lesion of the skin that is located in a specific region rather than being generalized.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating hormone concentration
nodes.def: Concentration of a hormone in the blood circulation outside of normal limits.

nodes.label: Abnormal pinna morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the pinna, which is also referred to as the auricle or external ear.

nodes.label: Triggered by
nodes.def: A trigger is defined as an external factor that leads to the manifestation of a sign or symptom in a person with a susceptibility to developing that manifestation.

nodes.label: Elevated urinary carboxylic acid
nodes.def: An increased amount of carboxylic acid in the urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the kidney.

nodes.label: Abnormal enzyme activity in cultured fibroblasts
nodes.def: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in cultured fibroblasts. Fibroblasts are easy to grow in culture and are the main cell type involved in producing extracellular matrix. They are used as a convenient model system for measuring enzyme activity for enzymes that are not expressed in blood cells. Usually, the test is done in fibroblasts for convenience rather than for the investigation of a pathophysiology specific to fibroblasts.

nodes.label: Abnormal foot morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skeleton of foot.

nodes.label: Abnormal eyelid morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the eyelids.

nodes.label: Dicarboxylic aciduria
nodes.def: An increased concentration of dicarboxylic acid in the urine.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the skin
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skin.

nodes.label: Abnormal humerus morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the structure of the humerus (i.e., upper arm bone).

nodes.label: Abnormal skin morphology
nodes.def: Any morphological abnormality of the skin.

nodes.label: Past medical history
nodes.def: In a medical encounter, the physician generally will interview the patient about his or her current problem, and may perform additional testing. The past medical history (PMH) in contrast records information about the patient's medical, personal and family history that might be relevant to the presenting illness or to provide optimal clinical management. The PMH generally includes (if relevant) other major illnesses, hospitalizations, surgeries, injuries, allergies, gynecologic and obstetric history, family history, personal history including occupational history, alcohol and drug use, etc.

nodes.label: Edema
nodes.def: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.

nodes.label: Abnormal finger morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of a finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal nail morphology
nodes.def: Abnormal structure or appearance of the nail.

nodes.label: Abnormal metacarpal morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormal shape or structure of the metacarpal bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal systemic arterial morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries.

nodes.label: Abnormal testis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the testicle (the male gonad).

nodes.label: Abnormal toe morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of a toe.

nodes.label: Abnormal retinal morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the retina.

nodes.label: Abnormal hand morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormal nervous system physiology
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal metatarsal morphology
nodes.def: Abnormalities of the metatarsal bones (i.e. of five tubular bones located between the tarsal bones of the hind- and mid-foot and the phalanges of the toes).

nodes.label: Abnormal conjunctiva morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the conjunctiva.

nodes.label: Abnormal calvaria morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the morphology (structure) of the calvaria (skullcap), that is, of that part of the skull that is made up of the superior portions of the frontal bone, occipital bone, and parietal bones and covers the cranial cavity that contains the brain.

nodes.label: Abnormal muscle fiber morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the skeletal muscle cell. Muscle fibers are subdivided into two types. Type I fibers are fatigue-resistant and rich in oxidative enzymes (they stain light with the myosin ATPase reaction), and type II fibers are fast-contracting, fatigue-prone, and rich in glycolytic enzymes (these fibers stain darkly). Normal muscle tissue has a random distribution of type I and type II fibers.

nodes.label: Increased inflammatory response
nodes.def: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

nodes.label: Abnormal liver morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the bile-secreting organ that is important for detoxification, for fat, carbohydrate, and protein metabolism, and for glycogen storage.

nodes.label: Abnormal rib morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the rib.

nodes.label: Abnormal carpal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality affecting the carpal bones of the wrist (scaphoid, lunate, triquetral, pisiform, trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, hamate).

nodes.label: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies
nodes.def: Abnormal morphology of vertebral body.

nodes.label: Abnormal finger phalanx morphology
nodes.def: Abnormalities affecting the phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Gait disturbance
nodes.def: The term gait disturbance can refer to any disruption of the ability to walk.

nodes.label: Hemangioma
nodes.def: A hemangioma is a benign tumor characterized by blood-filled spaces lined by benign endothelial cells. A hemangioma characterized by large endothelial spaces (caverns) is called a cavernous hemangioma (in contrast to a hemangioma with small endothelial spaces, which is called capillary hemangioma).

nodes.label: Pregnancy history
nodes.def: Medical history of maternal diseases, exposures, or other relevant findings during the pregnancy of which the index person was the product.

nodes.label: Ectopic calcification
nodes.def: Deposition of calcium salts in a tissue or location in which calcification does not normally occur.

nodes.label: Constitutional symptom
nodes.def: A symptom or manifestation indicating a systemic or general effect of a disease and that may affect the general well-being or status of an individual.

nodes.label: Abnormal pulmonary thoracic imaging finding
nodes.def: This term groups terms representing abnormal findings derived from chest X-ray investigation of the lung. In general, lung abnormalities can manifest as opacities (areas of increased density) or as regions with decreased density.

nodes.label: Increased urinary non-proteinogenic amino acid level
nodes.def: An increased level in the urine of an alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

nodes.label: Abnormal tongue morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the tongue.

nodes.label: Phenotypic abnormality
nodes.def: A phenotypic abnormality.

nodes.label: Abnormal mandible morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the mandible, the bone of the lower jaw.

nodes.label: Abnormal esophagus morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the esophagus.

nodes.label: Abnormal respiratory system physiology
nodes.def: Abnormal function of the respiratory system.

nodes.label: Abnormal cellular physiology
nodes.def: An abnormality in a cellular process.

nodes.label: Abnormal skeletal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.

nodes.label: Localized
nodes.def: Being confined or restricted to a particular location.

nodes.label: Medication history
nodes.def: Information about current or past medications taken by an individual.

nodes.label: Recent past medical history
nodes.def: History of events that precede the current presenting condition and are thought to be of potential relevance, having occurred in the hours, days, or weeks before the current condition.

nodes.label: Abnormal peripheral nervous system morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the peripheral nervous system, which is composed of the nerves that lead to or branch off from the central nervous system. This includes the cranial nerves (olfactory and optic nerves are technically part of the central nervous system).

nodes.label: Abnormality of the vertebral column
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the vertebral column.

nodes.label: Abnormal joint morphology
nodes.def: An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.

nodes.label: Abnormal erythrocyte morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of erythrocytes (red-blood cells).

nodes.label: Abnormal intestine morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the intestine. The closely related term enteropathy is used to refer to any disease of the intestine.

nodes.label: Abnormal pulmonary interstitial morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the lung parenchyma extending to the pulmonary interstitium and leading to diffuse pulmonary fibrosis.

nodes.label: Abnormal epiphysis morphology of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand. Note that this includes the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits).

nodes.label: Abnormal larynx morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the structure of the larynx.

nodes.label: Abnormal penis morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the male external sex organ.

nodes.label: Abnormal metaphysis morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of one or more metaphysis, i.e., of the somewhat wider portion of a long bone that is adjacent to the epiphyseal growth plate and grows during childhood.

nodes.label: Muscle weakness
nodes.def: Reduced strength of muscles.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the telencephalon, which is also known as the cerebrum.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the upper limb
nodes.def: An abnormality of the arm.

nodes.label: Abnormal epiphysis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of epiphysis, which is the expanded articular end of a long bone that developes from a secondary ossification center, and which during the period of growth is either entirely cartilaginous or is separated from the shaft by a cartilaginous disk.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the elbow
nodes.def: An anomaly of the joint that connects the upper and the lower arm.

nodes.label: Neoplasm by anatomical site
nodes.def: Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm.

nodes.label: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
nodes.def: The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.

nodes.label: Long-bone fracture
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of a lone bone (e.g., the femur, tibia, fibula, humerus, radius, and ulna).

nodes.label: Abnormal bronchus morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the bronchi, i.e., of the airways leading from the trachea to the lungs.

nodes.label: Positive infectious agent test
nodes.def: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in a specimen positive.

nodes.label: Exposure history
nodes.def: Information about current and past exposure to metals, dust, fibers, fumes, chemicals, biologic hazards, radiation, noise, and/or vibration at work or home.

nodes.label: Abnormal vagina morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the vagina.

nodes.label: Abnormal heart morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of the radius
nodes.def: An abnormality of the radius.

nodes.label: Abnormal femur morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the structure of the femur.

nodes.label: Abnormal cardiovascular system physiology
nodes.def: Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.

nodes.label: Abnormal eye physiology
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of the eye.

nodes.label: Abnormal long bone morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of size or shape of the long bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal CSF amino acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of amino acids in the cerebrospinal fluid.

nodes.label: Hyperkeratosis
nodes.def: Hyperkeratosis is a histopathological term defining a thickened stratum corneum and may be present in many different skin conditions, with many possible overlaps. Hyperkeratosis refers to the increased thickness of the stratum corneum, the outer layer of the skin. Hyperkeratosis is subclassified as orthokeratotic or parakeratotic. Orthokeratotic hyperkeratosis refers to the thickening of the keratin layer with preserved keratinocyte maturation, while parakeratotic hyperkeratosis shows retained nuclei as a sign of delayed maturation of keratinocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebellum morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the cerebellum.

nodes.label: Abnormal spinal cord morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the spinal cord (myelon).

nodes.label: Abnormal large intestine morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the large intestine.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the gastrointestinal tract
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the gastrointestinal tract.

nodes.label: Abnormal retinal vascular morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of retinal vasculature.

nodes.label: Abnormal gallbladder morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the gallbladder.

nodes.label: Abdominal symptom
nodes.def: A subjective manifestation of disease localized to the abdomen.

nodes.label: Abnormal erythrocyte enzyme concentration or activity
nodes.def: An altered level of any enzyme to act as catalysts within erythrocytes. This term includes changes due to altered activity of an enzyme.

nodes.label: Aggravated by
nodes.def: An aggravating factor is defined as an external factor that leads to a sign or symptom that is already present getting worse or becoming more severe.

nodes.label: Abnormal urine carbohydrate level
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carbohydrate in the urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal muscle fiber protein expression
nodes.def: An anomalous amount of protein present in or on the surface of muscle fibers. This feature may be appreciate upon immunohistochemical investigation of muscle biopsy tissue.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating non-proteinogenic amino acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of an alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

nodes.label: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration
nodes.def: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in liver tissue.

nodes.label: Abnormal lung morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the lung.

nodes.label: Abnormality of vision
nodes.def: Abnormality of eyesight (visual perception).

nodes.label: Abnormal small intestine morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the small intestine.

nodes.label: Abnormal vertebral morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of one or more of the vertebrae.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral white matter morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the cerebral white matter.

nodes.label: Increased bone mineral density
nodes.def: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones which is often referred to as osteosclerosis. Osteosclerosis can be detected on radiological examination as an increased whiteness (density) of affected bones.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating interleukin concentration
nodes.def: The concentration of an interleukin (a class of cytokines) is outside the limits of normal.

nodes.label: Abnormal stool composition
nodes.def: Abnormal level of metabolite or other abnormal analyte result in a stool test.

nodes.label: Ameliorated by
nodes.def: An ameliorating factor is defined as an external factor that leads to a sign or symptom that is already present improving or becoming more bearable

nodes.label: Focal cognitive seizure
nodes.def: A focal cognitive seizure involves an alteration in a cognitive function (which can be a deficit or a positive phenomenon such as forced thought), which occurs at seizure onset. To be classified as a focal cognitive seizure, the change in cognitive function should be specific and out of proportion to other relatively unimpaired aspects of cognition, because all cognition is impaired in a focal impaired awareness seizure.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of ulna
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the ulna, a bone of the forearm the extends from the elbow to the little finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of movement
nodes.def: An abnormality of movement with a neurological basis characterized by changes in coordination and speed of voluntary movements.

nodes.label: Bloodstream virus-specific antibody positivity
nodes.def: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a virus.

nodes.label: Abnormal lip morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the lip.

nodes.label: Abnormal optic nerve morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the optic nerve.

nodes.label: Delusion
nodes.def: A delusion is a fixed false belief held despite evidence to the contrary. The term delusion broadly encompasses all false judgments that possess the following external characteristics to a significant, albeit unspecified, extent: (1) they are held with an exceptional level of conviction, accompanied by an unparalleled subjective certainty; (2) there is an inability to consider alternative experiences or compelling counter-arguments; (3) the content of the belief is impossible.

nodes.label: Abnormality of skin pigmentation
nodes.def: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin.

nodes.label: Abnormal aortic morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the aorta.

nodes.label: Abnormal bleeding
nodes.def: An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects.

nodes.label: Abnormal basal ganglia morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the basal ganglia.

nodes.label: Abnormal cornea morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the cornea, which is the transparent tissue at the front of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber.

nodes.label: Hamartoma
nodes.def: A disordered proliferation of mature tissues that is native to the site of origin, e.g., exostoses, nevi and soft tissue hamartomas. Although most hamartomas are benign, some histologic subtypes, e.g., neuromuscular hamartoma, may proliferate aggressively such as mesenchymal cystic hamartoma, Sclerosing epithelial hamartoma, Sclerosing metanephric hamartoma.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating carbohydrate concentration
nodes.def: A deviation from the normal concentration of a carbohydrate in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the distal phalanx of finger
nodes.def: Any anomaly of distal epiphysis of phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the middle phalanges of the hand
Abnormality of the epiphyses of the proximal phalanges of the hand
Abscess
nodes.def: An abscess is a localized collection of purulent material surrounded by inflammation and granulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal breast morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the structure of the breast.

nodes.label: Abnormal CSF protein concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal range of a protein concentration in the cerebrospinal fluid.

nodes.label: Focal aware cognitive seizure
nodes.def: A focal aware cognitive seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

nodes.label: Increased urine proteinogenic amino acid derivative level
nodes.def: An elevated urine level of a compound that is derived from an amino acid.

nodes.label: Abnormality on pulmonary function testing
nodes.def: Any anomaly measure by pulmonary function testing, which includes spirometry, measures of diffusing capacity, and plethysmography.

nodes.label: Ameliorated by exposure to medication
nodes.def: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a medication. Terms in this subhierarchy are intended to be used for cases in which the fact that a manifestation of a disease responds to a specific treatment can be used in the differential diagnosis.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the plantar skin of foot
nodes.def: An abnormality of the plantar part of foot, that is of the soles of the feet.

nodes.label: Abnormal pulmonary artery morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the structure of the pulmonary artery.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure
nodes.def: A focal cognitive seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

nodes.label: Abnormal scrotum morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the scrotum, i.e., the sac that contains the testes, epididymis, and the lower part of the spermatic cord.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal glomerulus morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the glomerulus.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the dentition
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the teeth.

nodes.label: Abnormal forehead morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the forehead.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the endocrine system
nodes.def: An abnormality of the endocrine system.

nodes.label: Abnormal skull morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skull, the bony framework of the head which is comprised of the neurocranium (with eight cranial bones) and the viscerocranium (facial skeleton) that comprises fourteen facial bones with the mandible as its largest bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal diaphysis morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the structure or form of the diaphysis, i.e., of the main or mid-section (shaft) of a long bone.

nodes.label: Hemolytic anemia
nodes.def: A type of anemia caused by premature destruction of red blood cells (hemolysis).

nodes.label: Morphological central nervous system abnormality
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the central nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormality of eye movement
nodes.def: An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eye movements or their control.

nodes.label: Abnormal myocardium morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the muscle layer of the heart wall.

nodes.label: Abnormal stomach morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the stomach.

nodes.label: Recurrent infections
nodes.def: Increased susceptibility to infections as manifested by repeated bouts of infection.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the lower limb
nodes.def: An abnormality of the leg.

nodes.label: Abnormal tibia morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the tibia (shinbone).

nodes.label: Abnormal speech pattern
nodes.def: An abnormality in the sound (volume) or cadence (rate) of speech.

nodes.label: Abnormal bone marrow cell morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the form or number of cells in the bone marrow.

nodes.label: Peripheral neuropathy
nodes.def: Peripheral neuropathy is a general term for any disorder of the peripheral nervous system. The main clinical features used to classify peripheral neuropathy are distribution, type (mainly demyelinating versus mainly axonal), duration, and course.

nodes.label: Abnormal distal phalanx morphology of finger
nodes.def: Any anomaly of distal phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal proximal phalanx morphology of the hand
Abnormal circulating monocarboxylic acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a monocarboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: EEG with focal epileptiform discharges
nodes.def: EEG discharges recorded in particular areas of a localized (focal) abnormality in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

nodes.label: Allergy
nodes.def: An allergy is an immune response or reaction to substances that are usually not harmful.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the middle phalanges of the toes
Abnormal biliary tract morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the biliary tree.

nodes.label: Abnormal brain morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the brain, which has as its parts the forebrain, midbrain, and hindbrain.

nodes.label: Abnormal oral mucosa morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the oral mucosa.

nodes.label: Focal motor seizure
nodes.def: A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by a motor sign as its initial semiological manifestation.

nodes.label: Abnormal neck morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the neck region.

nodes.label: Pain characteristic
nodes.def: A pain characteristic is defined as a subjective category or type of pain.

nodes.label: Abnormal spleen morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the structure of the spleen.

nodes.label: Abnormal bladder morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the bladder.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal insterstitial morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the interstitium of the kidney. The renal interstitium is defined as the intertubular, extraglomerular, extravascular space of the kidney. It is bounded on all sides by tubular and vascular basement membranes and is filled with cells, extracellular matrix, and interstitial fluid.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal tubular epithelial morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the renal tubular epithelial cells (RTEC), a layer of cells in the outer layer of the renal tubule. These cells play a role in the absorption of substances such as glucose and amino from the primary urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal glomerular basement membrane morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormal sttructure of the glomerular basement membrane.

nodes.label: Positive bloodstream nucleic acid pathogen test
nodes.def: Positive (abnormal) result of a test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

nodes.label: Abnormal eyebrow morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the eyebrow.

nodes.label: Atypical behavior
nodes.def: Atypical behavior is an abnormality in a person's actions that can be controlled or modulated by the will of the individual. While abnormal behaviors can be difficult to control, they are distinct from other abnormal actions that cannot be affected by the individual's will.

nodes.label: Abnormal clavicle morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the clavicles (collar bones).

nodes.label: Abnormality of the tarsal bones
nodes.def: An abnormality of the tarsus are the cluster of seven bones in the foot between the tibia and fibula and the metatarsus, including the calcaneus (heel) bone and the talus (ankle) bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal facial shape
nodes.def: An abnormal morphology (form) of the face or its components.

nodes.label: Sensorineural hearing impairment
nodes.def: A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve.

nodes.label: Abnormality iris morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the iris, which is the pigmented muscular tissue between the cornea and the lens, that is perforated by an opening called the pupil.

nodes.label: Abnormal brainstem morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the brainstem.

nodes.label: Abnormal humeral epiphysis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the humeral epiphysis.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 2nd finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, middle, and distal phalanges of the 2nd finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal dental morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the morphology of the tooth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the hallux
Abnormal middle phalanx morphology of the hand
nodes.def: An anomaly of middle phalanx of finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 2nd toe
Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 3rd toe
Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 4th toe
Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 5th toe
Abnormal helix morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the helix. The helix is the outer rim of the ear that extends from the insertion of the ear on the scalp (root) to the termination of the cartilage at the earlobe.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, middle, and distal phalanges of the 5th finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 4th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, middle, and distal phalanges of the 4th finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 3rd finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, middle, and distal phalanges of the 3rd finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal physiology
nodes.def: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.

nodes.label: Bone fracture
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of the continuity of a bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal best corrected visual acuity test
Abnormal uterus morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the structure of the uterus

nodes.label: Abnormal metabolic brain imaging by MRS
nodes.def: An anomaly of metabolism in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

nodes.label: Clinical modifier
nodes.def: This subontology is designed to provide terms to characterize and specify the phenotypic abnormalities defined in the Phenotypic abnormality subontology, with respect to severity, laterality, age of onset, and other aspects.

nodes.label: Abnormal urine carboxylic acid level
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the urine.

nodes.label: Fetal exposure history
nodes.def: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to a medication or other substance.

nodes.label: Functional abnormality of the bladder
nodes.def: Dysfunction of the urinary bladder.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal tubule morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the renal tubules.

nodes.label: Abnormal oral cavity morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the oral cavity, i.e., the opening or hollow part of the mouth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the face
nodes.def: An abnormality of the face.

nodes.label: Abnormal macular morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the macula lutea, which is an oval-shaped highly pigmented yellow spot near the center of the retina.

nodes.label: Abnormal pattern of respiration
nodes.def: An anomaly of the rhythm or depth of breathing.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the central nervous system
nodes.def: Absence or underdevelopment of tissue in the central nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal fibula morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the calf bone (fibula), one of the two bones of the calf.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating cholesterol concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of cholesterol in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal EKG
nodes.def: Abnormal rhythm of the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormality of thumb epiphysis
nodes.def: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, and distal phalanges of the thumb and/or the 1st metacarpal.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the thumb
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the distal phalanx of thumb.

nodes.label: Abnormal adrenal morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the adrenal glands.

nodes.label: Abnormal eye morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the globe of the eye, or bulbus oculi.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanges of the toes
Abnormality of toe proximal phalanx
nodes.def: A morphological anomaly of one or more proximal phalanges of one or more toes.

nodes.label: Abnormal muscle physiology
nodes.def: A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

nodes.label: Abnormal facial skeleton morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of one or more of the set of bones that make up the facial skeleton.

nodes.label: Focal aware motor seizure
nodes.def: A type of focal motor seizure in which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

nodes.label: Abnormal epidermal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the morphology of the epidermis.

nodes.label: Abnormal arterial physiology
nodes.def: An anomaly of arterial function.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure
nodes.def: A type of focal motor seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

nodes.label: Increased proteinogenic amino acid level in urine
nodes.def: An elevated level of a proteinogenic amino acid in the urine. These are the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating organic compound concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation of the concentration of an orrganic compound from the normal range. An organic compound is defined as any compound that contains a carbon atom.

nodes.label: Abnormal urinary organic compound level
nodes.def: The amount of an organic compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal. An organic compound is defined here as a chemical compound that contains a carbon-hydrogen or carbon-carbon bond, although some other definitions exist. Examples of organic compounds includes alkanes, alkenes, alkynes, aromatic compounds, alcohols, ketones, aldehydes, carboxylic acids, and esters.

nodes.label: Blood xenobiotic
nodes.def: The presence of a xenobiotic in blood.

nodes.label: Fracture type
nodes.def: Category of fracture. Terms from this subontology can be used together with terms in the subontology that descends from Bone fracture (HP:0020110).

nodes.label: Abnormal placenta morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the placenta, the organ that connects the developing fetus to the uterine wall to enable nutrient uptake, waste elimination, and gas exchange.

nodes.label: Abnormality of facial musculature
nodes.def: An anomaly of a muscle that is innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

nodes.label: Abnormal sclera morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the sclera.

nodes.label: Abnormal anterior chamber morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the anterior chamber, which is the space in the eye that is behind the cornea and in front of the iris.

nodes.label: Abnormal sternum morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the sternum, also known as the breastbone.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the urethra
nodes.def: An abnormality of the urethra, i.e., of the tube which connects the urinary bladder to the outside of the body.

nodes.label: Limitation of joint mobility
nodes.def: A reduction in the freedom of movement of one or more joints.

nodes.label: Toe syndactyly
nodes.def: Webbing or fusion of the toes, involving soft parts only or including bone structure. Bony fusions are referred to as "bony" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the toes in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as "Symphalangism".

nodes.label: Hearing impairment
nodes.def: A decreased magnitude of the sensory perception of sound.

nodes.label: Abnormal eyelash morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the eyelashes.

nodes.label: Abnormality of connective tissue
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the soft tissues, including both connective tissue (tendons, ligaments, fascia, fibrous tissues, and fat).

nodes.label: Nevus
nodes.def: A nevus is a type of hamartoma that is a circumscribed stable malformation of the skin.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral cortex morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the cerebral cortex.

nodes.label: Abnormal lymph node morphology
nodes.def: A structural lymph node abnormality.

nodes.label: Abnormal 5th finger phalanx morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 5th (little) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the fifth finger. This epiphysis is located on the proximal end of the phalanx.

nodes.label: Involuntary movements
nodes.def: Involuntary contractions of muscle leading to involuntary movements of extremities, neck, trunk, or face.

nodes.label: Abnormal vitreous humor morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the vitreous body.

nodes.label: Poikilocytosis
nodes.def: The presence of abnormally shaped erythrocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormal limb bone morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of bones of the arms or legs.

nodes.label: Abnormal patella morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the patella (knee cap).

nodes.label: Abnormality of urine homeostasis
nodes.def: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.

nodes.label: Abnormality of mitochondrial metabolism
nodes.def: A functional anomaly of mitochondria.

nodes.label: Nail dysplasia
nodes.def: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the nail.

nodes.label: Abnormal phalangeal joint morphology of the hand
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb
nodes.def: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the thumb. This epiphysis is located on the proximal end of the phalanx.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
nodes.def: This term applies if the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the thumb, which is located at the proximal end of the phalanx, does not appear in concordance with gender and age dependant norms as seen on x-rays. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits.

nodes.label: Abnormal upper limb metaphysis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of one or more metaphyses of the arms.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
nodes.def: In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits). The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end (as seen in the proximal phalanges of the other digits), whereas the epiphyses of the other metacarpal bones are located at the distal end. This term applies if the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal is in any way abnormal, referring to age and gender depending norms, as seen on x-rays.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of phalanx of the 2nd toe
nodes.def: An anomaly of a phalanx of second toe.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 3rd toe
Neoplasm of the skeletal system
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skeleton.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the umbilical cord
nodes.def: An abnormality of the umbilical cord, which is the cord connecting the developing embryo or fetus to the placenta.

nodes.label: Abnormality of immune system physiology
nodes.def: A functional abnormality of the immune system.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the common coagulation pathway
nodes.def: An abnormality of blood coagulation, common pathway.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating dicarboxylic acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a dicarboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Temporal pattern
nodes.def: The speed at which disease manifestations appear and develop.

nodes.label: Amyloidosis
nodes.def: The presence of amyloid deposition in one or more tissues. Amyloidosis may be defined as the extracellular deposition of amyloid in one or more sites of the body.

nodes.label: Abnormal incisor morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth.

nodes.label: Abnormal digit morphology
nodes.def: A morphological abnormality of a digit, i.e., of a finger or toe.

nodes.label: Abnormal 4th finger phalanx morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 4th (ring) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the fifth finger. This epiphysis is located on the proximal end of the phalanx.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormal 3rd finger phalanx morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 3rd (middle) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
Fetal ultrasound soft marker
nodes.def: An finding upon obstetric ultrasound examination performed at around 16 to 20 weeks of gestation that is abnormal but not clearly identifiable as a fetal anatomic malformation or growth restriction. Such findings are known as soft markers since they are associated with increased risk for fetal aneuploidy or other disorders.

nodes.label: Abnormal glomerular visceral epithelial cell morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the podocyte, which is a highly specialized cell of the Bowman capsule and which forms multiple interdigitating foot processes. Podocytes are interconnected by slit diaphragms and cover the exterior basement membrane surface of the glomerular capillary.

nodes.label: Functional abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
nodes.def: Abnormal functionality of the gastrointestinal tract.

nodes.label: Marker expression
nodes.def: Detection of a marker such as a protein by immunohistochemistry or related investigation techniques. The presence or absence of such markers can be used to identify cell types on the basis of a profile of expressed markers. These terms do not imply abnormality and can be used for any cell type or organ.

nodes.label: Fractured epiphysis
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of the epiphysis.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the chin
nodes.def: An abnormality of the chin, i.e., of the inferior portion of the face lying inferior to the lower lip and including the central prominence of the lower jaw.

nodes.label: Abnormal scapula morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the scapula, also known as the shoulder blade.

nodes.label: Seizure
nodes.def: A seizure is an intermittent abnormality of nervous system physiology characterized by a transient occurrence of signs and/or symptoms due to abnormal excessive or synchronous neuronal activity in the brain.

nodes.label: Ataxia
nodes.def: Ataxia refers to impaired coordination of voluntary muscle movement. Cerebellar ataxia refers to ataxia due to dysfunction of the cerebellum. This causes a variety of elementary neurological deficits including asynergy (lack of coordination between muscles, limbs and joints), dysmetria (lack of ability to judge distances that can lead to under- or overshoot in grasping movements), and dysdiadochokinesia (inability to perform rapid movements requiring antagonizing muscle groups to be switched on and off repeatedly).

nodes.label: Myoclonus
nodes.def: Very brief, involuntary random muscular contractions occurring at rest, in response to sensory stimuli, or accompanying voluntary movements.

nodes.label: Abnormal delivery
nodes.def: An abnormality of the birth process.

nodes.label: Abnormal enchondral ossification
nodes.def: An abnormality of the process of endochondral ossification, which is a type of replacement ossification in which bone tissue replaces cartilage.

nodes.label: EMG abnormality
nodes.def: Abnormal results of investigations using electromyography (EMG).

nodes.label: Lymphadenopathy
nodes.def: Enlargement (swelling) of a lymph node.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 5th (little) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormal shoulder morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the shoulder, which is defined as the structures surrounding the shoulder joint where the humerus attaches to the scapula.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Skeletal muscle atrophy
nodes.def: The presence of skeletal muscular atrophy (which is also known as amyotrophy).

nodes.label: Abnormal carotid artery morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the carotid arteries, including the common carotid artery and its' arterial branches.

nodes.label: Broad phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Increased width of the phalanges of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the first metatarsal bone
nodes.def: An anomaly of the first metatarsal bone.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 4th toe
Abnormality of the phalanges of the 5th toe
Disturbed sensory perception
nodes.def: Alteration or impairment in the processing or interpretation of sensory information can lead to abnormal perceptions or experiences.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the femoral head
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

nodes.label: Intracranial cystic lesion
nodes.def: A cystic lesion originating within the brain.

nodes.label: Abnormal meningeal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the Meninges, including any abnormality of the Dura mater, the Arachnoid mater, and the Pia mater.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal tubular resorption
nodes.def: An abnormality of renal absorption.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the fifth finger. This epiphysis is located on the proximal end of the phalanx.

nodes.label: Finger aplasia
nodes.def: A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of fingers (i.e., aplasia of one or more fingers).

nodes.label: Abnormal central motor function
nodes.def: An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.

nodes.label: Abnormal lymph-node cellular finding
nodes.def: Any phenotypic abnormality within cells located in a lymph node.

nodes.label: Focal autonomic seizure
nodes.def: An autonomic seizure is a type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by alteration of autonomic nervous system function as the initial semiological feature.

nodes.label: Urine xenobiotic
nodes.def: The presence of a xenobiotic in urine.

nodes.label: Elevated urinary monocarboxylic acid level
nodes.def: Abnormally increased amount of a monocarboxylic acid in the urine. Monocarboxylic acids are molecules with one COOH functional group.

nodes.label: Abnormal fetal morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the fetus.

nodes.label: Inheritance qualifier
nodes.def: The terms in this hierarchy can be used to specify the context in which inheritance of a disease is typically observed.

nodes.label: Abnormal skin morphology of the palm
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skin of the palm, that is, the skin of the front of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormal enzyme activity in muscle tissue
nodes.def: Deviation from the normal activity of an enzyme in muscle tissue.

nodes.label: Unusual infection
nodes.def: A type of infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection. There are five general subtypes. (i) Opportunistic infection, meaning infection by a pathogen that is not normally able to cause infection in a healthy host (e.g., pneumonia by Pneumocystis jirovecii or CMV); (ii) Unusual location (focus) of an infection (e.g., an aspergillus brain abscess); (iii) a protracted course or lack of adequate response to treatment (e.g., chronic rhinosinusitis); (iv) Unusual severity or intensity of an infection; and (v) unusual recurrence of infections.

nodes.label: Past surgical history
nodes.def: information about the patient's previous surgical treatments that might be relevant to the presenting illness or to provide optimal clinical management.

nodes.label: Positive CSF infectious agent test
nodes.def: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) positive.

nodes.label: Retinopathy of prematurity
nodes.def: An avascular or abnormally vascularized retina that occurs in premature infants and can lead to blindness.

nodes.label: Aggravated by exposure to medication
nodes.def: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with a medication.

nodes.label: Renal cyst
nodes.def: A fluid filled sac in the kidney.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the gingiva
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the gingiva (also known as gums).

nodes.label: Abnormal palate morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the palate, i.e., of roof of the mouth.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the philtrum
nodes.def: An abnormality of the philtrum.

nodes.label: Abnormal maxilla morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the Maxilla (upper jaw bone).

nodes.label: Abnormality of the periorbital region
nodes.def: An abnormality of the region situated around the orbit of the eye.

nodes.label: Palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
nodes.def: Abnormal thickening of the skin localized to the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot.

nodes.label: Encephalopathy
nodes.def: Encephalopathy is a term that means brain disease, damage, or malfunction. In general, encephalopathy is manifested by an altered mental state.

nodes.label: Arthritis
nodes.def: Inflammation of a joint.

nodes.label: Joint stiffness
nodes.def: Joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in a joint or joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity. Joint stiffness typically subsides over time.

nodes.label: Abnormal hair morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the hair.

nodes.label: Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues
nodes.def: An abnormality of the hematopoietic system.

nodes.label: Abnormal pleura morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the pulmonary pleura, the thin, transparent membrane which covers the lungs and lines the inside of the chest walls.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebral ventricle morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the cerebral ventricles.

nodes.label: Abnormal nasal tip morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the nasal tip.

nodes.label: Strabismus
nodes.def: A misalignment of the eyes so that the visual axes deviate from bifoveal fixation. The classification of strabismus may be based on a number of features including the relative position of the eyes, whether the deviation is latent or manifest, intermittent or constant, concomitant or otherwise and according to the age of onset and the relevance of any associated refractive error.

nodes.label: Cataract
nodes.def: A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule.

nodes.label: Sleep abnormality
nodes.def: An abnormal pattern in the quality, quantity, or characteristics of sleep.

nodes.label: Abnormal tracheal morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the trachea.

nodes.label: Impaired platelet aggregation
nodes.def: An impairment in the rate and degree to which platelets aggregate after the addition of an agonist that stimulates platelet clumping. Platelet aggregation is measured using aggregometer to measure the optical density of platelet-rich plasma, whereby platelet aggregation causes the plasma to become more transparent.

nodes.label: Cerebral calcification
nodes.def: The presence of calcium deposition within the cerebrum.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
Abnormal circulating carboxylic acid concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal cerebrospinal fluid morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

nodes.label: Abnormal bone structure
nodes.def: Any anomaly in the composite material or the layered arrangement of the bony skeleton.

nodes.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the lower limbs
nodes.def: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the lower limbs.

nodes.label: Abnormal humeral diaphysis morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the humeral diaphysis.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 2nd finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 2nd (index) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Abnormality of thumb phalanx
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of one or more phalanges of the thumb.

nodes.label: Renal neoplasm
nodes.def: The presence of a neoplasm of the kidney.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Small or missing phalangeal bones of the fingers of the hand.

nodes.label: Teratoma
nodes.def: The presence of a teratoma.

nodes.label: Abnormal 1st metacarpal morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the first metacarpal.

nodes.label: Abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the hallux
nodes.def: An abnormal shape or form of the proximal phalanx of the big toe.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the hallux
Cutaneous finger syndactyly
nodes.def: A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints, or a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that lies significantly distal to the flexion crease that overlies the metacarpophalangeal joint of the adjacent fingers.

nodes.label: Fibroma
nodes.def: Benign tumors that are composed of fibrous or connective tissue. They can grow in all organs, arising from mesenchyme tissue. The term "fibroblastic" or "fibromatous" is used to describe tumors of the fibrous connective tissue. When the term fibroma is used without modifier, it is usually considered benign, with the term fibrosarcoma reserved for malignant tumors.

nodes.label: Abnormal hand bone ossification
nodes.def: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of hand.

nodes.label: Erythema
nodes.def: Redness of the skin, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the musculature of the limbs
Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the hallux
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the 1st metatarsal
nodes.def: In contrast to the metatarsals 2-5, the first metatarsal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, whereas the proximal phalanx of the big toe is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits. This term applies to abnormalities of the epiphysis of the first metatarsal bone.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the hallux
nodes.def: In contrast to the metatarsals 2-5, the first metatarsal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, whereas the proximal phalanx of the big toe is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits. This term applies to abnormalities affecting the proximal phalanx of the hallux.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the toes
Abnormal neutrophil morphology
nodes.def: An abnormal form or size of neutrophils.

nodes.label: Abnormal sperm head morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the sperm head.

nodes.label: Generalized abnormality of skin
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skin that is not localized to any one particular region.

nodes.label: Regional abnormality of skin
nodes.def: An abnormality of the skin that is restricted to a particular body region.

nodes.label: Crystalluria
nodes.def: The presence of crystals in the urine.

nodes.label: Abnormal ureter morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.

nodes.label: Abnormal fetal skeletal morphology
nodes.def: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal skeleton. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other terms from the skeletal hierarchy can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

nodes.label: Abnormal cardiomyocyte morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of cardiomyocytes, which are terminally differentiated muscle cells in the heart that are interconnected end to end by gap junctions, which allows coordinated contraction of heart tissue.

nodes.label: Abnormal optic disc morphology
nodes.def: A morphological abnormality of the optic disc, i.e., of the portion of the optic nerve clinically visible on fundoscopic examination.

nodes.label: Increased circulating specific IgE antibody concentration
Abnormal blood vessel morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of a blood vessel (artery, arteriole, capillary, venule, or vein).

nodes.label: Abnormal fetal gastrointestinal system morphology
nodes.def: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal gastrointestinal system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

nodes.label: Arteriovenous malformation
nodes.def: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 2nd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 2nd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 4th toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 4th toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 4th toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 5th toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 5th toe
Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 5th toe
Abnormal knee morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.

nodes.label: Abnormal ankle morphology
nodes.def: A structural anomaly of the ankle.

nodes.label: Abnormal tissue metabolite concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a metabolite in a tissue.

nodes.label: Abnormal emotional state
nodes.def: Emotions are complex psychological states that involve three distinct components: a subjective experience, a physiological response, and a behavioral or expressive response. In an abnormal emotional state, an affected individual shows altered intensity, frequency, or duration of emotional experiences.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of finger phalanx
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more phalanges of the fingers. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Fractured hindlimb bone
nodes.def: A partial or complete breakage of the hindlimb bone.

nodes.label: Focal automatism seizure
nodes.def: A focal seizure characterized at onset by coordinated motor activity. This often resembles a voluntary movement and may consist of an inappropriate continuation of preictal motor activity.

nodes.label: Neoplasm of the lung
nodes.def: Tumor of the lung.

nodes.label: Abnormal paranasal sinus morphology
nodes.def: Abnormality of the paranasal (cranial) sinuses, which are air-filled spaces that are located within the bones of the skull and face and communicate with the nasal cavity. They comprise the maxillary sinuses, the frontal sinuses, the ethmoid sinuses, and the sphenoid sinuses.

nodes.label: Nystagmus
nodes.def: Rhythmic, involuntary oscillations of one or both eyes related to abnormality in fixation, conjugate gaze, or vestibular mechanisms.

nodes.label: Tooth malposition
nodes.def: Abnormal alignment, positioning, or spacing of the teeth, i.e., misaligned teeth.

nodes.label: Compulsive behaviors
nodes.def: Behavior that consists of repetitive acts, characterized by the feeling that one "has to" perform them, while being aware that these acts are not in line with one's overall goal.

nodes.label: Abnormal thorax morphology
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the thorax (the region of the body formed by the sternum, the thoracic vertebrae and the ribs).

nodes.label: Abnormal internal genitalia
nodes.def: An anomaly of the adnexa, uterus, and vagina (in female) or seminal tract and prostate (in male).

nodes.label: Abnormal posterior cranial fossa morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fossa cranii posterior (the posterior fossa), which is made up primarily of the occipital bone and which surrounds to the foramen magnum.

nodes.label: Abnormal fundus morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the fundus of the eye.

nodes.label: Abnormal thumb morphology
nodes.def: An abnormal structure of the first digit of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormal cranial nerve morphology
nodes.def: Structural abnormality affecting one or more of the cranial nerves, which emerge directly from the brain stem.

nodes.label: Lissencephaly
nodes.def: A spectrum of malformations of cortical development caused by insufficient neuronal migration that subsumes the terms agyria, pachygyria and subcortical band heterotopia. See also neuropathological definitions for 2-, 3-, and 4-layered lissencephaly.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the musculature of the upper limbs
Abnormal tricuspid valve morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the tricuspid valve.

nodes.label: Abnormal hallux morphology
nodes.def: This term applies for all abnormalities of the big toe, also called hallux.

nodes.label: Abnormal rectum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormaltiy of the rectum, the final segment of the large intestine that stores solid waste until it passes through the anus.

nodes.label: Abnormal earlobe morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the lobule of pinna.

nodes.label: Astigmatism
nodes.def: A type of refraction error associated with abnormal curvatures on the anterior and/or posterior surface of the cornea.

nodes.label: Abnormal cartilage morphology
nodes.def: Any morphological abnormality of cartilage.

nodes.label: Abnormal mitral valve morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly of the mitral valve.

nodes.label: Myotonia
nodes.def: An involuntary and painless delay in the relaxation of skeletal muscle following contraction or electrical stimulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal venous morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of vein.

nodes.label: Deviation of finger
nodes.def: Deviated fingers is a term that should be used if one or more fingers of the hand are deviated from their normal position, either to the radial or ulnar side. A deviation of a finger can be caused by an abnormal form of one or more of the phalanges of the affected finger, or by a deviation or displacement of one or more phalanges.

nodes.label: Decreased circulating immunoglobulin concentration
nodes.def: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin in blood.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating nitrogen compound concentration
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a nitrogen compound in the blood circulation.

nodes.label: Abnormal nipple morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the nipple.

nodes.label: Abnormal cheek morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the cheek- one of two bilateral soft tissue facial structures in the region of the face inferior to the eyes and between the nose and the ear. "Buccal" means relating to the cheek. The cheek is part of the midface

nodes.label: Abnormality of thyroid physiology
nodes.def: An abnormal functionality of the thyroid gland.

nodes.label: Abnormal acetabulum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the acetabulum, i.e., the Acetabular part of hip bone, which together with the head of the femur forms the hip joint.

nodes.label: Abnormal hairshaft morphology
nodes.def: An abnormal structure of the hairshaft, i.e., of the nongrowing portion of a hair that protrudes from the skin.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of fingers
nodes.def: Small/hypoplastic or absent/aplastic fingers.

nodes.label: Abnormal pons morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the pons.

nodes.label: Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the central nervous system
Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the thumb
nodes.def: An anomaly of the shape or form of the proximal phalanx of the thumb.

nodes.label: Patchy sclerosis of finger phalanx
nodes.def: Uneven (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the phalanges of the hand.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 2nd toe
Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 2nd toe
Abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd toe
Epiphyseal stippling
nodes.def: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more epiphyses.

nodes.label: Abnormal circulating immunoglobulin concentration
nodes.def: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in blood.

nodes.label: Aplasia of the phalanges of the toes
nodes.def: Absence of a digit or of one or more phalanges of a toe.

nodes.label: Testicular neoplasm
nodes.def: The presence of a neoplasm of the testis.

nodes.label: Abnormal sacrum morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the sacral bone.

nodes.label: Abnormal adipose tissue morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of adipose tissue, which is loose connective tissue composed of adipocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger
nodes.def: Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the little (5th) finger.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 4th finger
Abnormal homeostasis
nodes.def: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

nodes.label: Broad phalanx of the toes
nodes.def: Increased width of phalanx of one or more toes.

nodes.label: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the toes
Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the toes
Cone-shaped epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the fingers of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of a phalanx.

nodes.label: Ivory epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
nodes.def: Sclerosis of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the fingers, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

nodes.label: Epiphyseal stippling of finger phalanges
nodes.def: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphyses of phalanges of the fingers.

nodes.label: Abnormal thyroid morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the thyroid gland.

nodes.label: Abnormal hemoglobin
nodes.def: Anomaly in the level or the function of hemoglobin, the oxygen-carrying protein of erythrocytes.

nodes.label: Abnormality of cranial sutures
nodes.def: Any anomaly of a cranial suture, that is one of the six membrane-covered openings in the incompletely ossified skull of the fetus or newborn infant.

nodes.label: Abnormality of mental function
nodes.def: Cognitive, psychiatric, or memory anomaly.

nodes.label: Abnormal uterine cervix morphology
nodes.def: An anomaly of the neck of the uterus (lower part of the uterus), called the uterine cervix.

nodes.label: Reflex seizure
nodes.def: Seizures precipitated by exogenous stimuli.

nodes.label: Focal sensory seizure
nodes.def: A focal sensory seizure is a type seizure beginning with a subjective sensation.

nodes.label: Abnormal T cell subset distribution
nodes.def: Abnormal increase or decrease of any T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

nodes.label: Abnormal gastrointestinal tract morphology
nodes.def: Abnormal structure of the gastrointestinal tract.

nodes.label: Pulmonary interstitial high-resolution computed tomography abnormality
nodes.def: High-resolution computed tomography (HRCT) can distinguish findings that characterize characterize interstitial lung diseases in a way not possible with other modalities.

nodes.label: Abnormal cell morphology
nodes.def: Any anomaly of cell structure.

nodes.label: Renal intratubular casts
nodes.def: Urinary casts are formed in the distal convoluted tubule or the collecting duct by solidification of protein in the lumen of the kidney tubules. This term refers to casts located within the tubuli of the kidney. More precisely, casts are defined as a material that completely fills and expands the tubular lumen with simplification of surrounding tubular epithelium. Casts are classified as either nuclear debris/granular brown material, red blood cell, white blood cell, myeloma, or myoglobin cast.

nodes.label: Abnormal urinary pyrimidine level
nodes.def: Any deviation from the normal amount of a pyrimidine compound in the urine. Pyrimidines and pyrimidine derivatives are compounds containing a pyrimidne ring, which is a six-member aromatic heterocycle which consists of two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 3) and four carbon atoms. The nucleotides cytosine, thymine and uracil are pyrimidines.

nodes.label: Monocarboxylic aciduria
nodes.def: Level of a monocarboxylic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal. A monocarboxylic acid is an oxoacid containing one carboxy group.

nodes.label: Sclerosis of toe phalanx
nodes.def: An elevation in bone density in one or more phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

nodes.label: Papule
nodes.def: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point.

nodes.label: Abnormality of muscle of facial expression
nodes.def: An abnormality of any of the muscles of facial expression, which are innervated by the seventh (VII) cranial nerve and control facial expression.

nodes.label: Positive CSF nucleic acid pathogen test
nodes.def: Positive (abnormal) result of a cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

nodes.label: Abnormal arcuate vein intima/media morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly located in the inner or middle layer of the arcuate veins of the kidney.

nodes.label: Abnormal renal arteriole intima/media morphology
nodes.def: Any structural anomaly located in the inner or middle layer of the arterioles of the kidney.

nodes.label: Focal aware autonomic seizure
nodes.def: A focal aware autonomic seizure has an initial manifestation pertaining to autonomic nervous system function, which may be objective (for example, pupillary dilation) or subjective (for example, nausea). As a type of focal aware seizure, awareness is retained throughout.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure
nodes.def: A focal autonomic seizure characterized by impaired awareness at some point within the seizure.

nodes.label: Focal impaired awareness automatism seizure
nodes.def: A focal seizure with automatism in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

nodes.label: Focal aware automatism seizure
nodes.def: A type of focal automatism seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

nodes.label: Ovarian neoplasm
nodes.def: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ovary.

nodes.label: Abnormal male external genitalia morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of male external genitalia.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the menstrual cycle
nodes.def: An abnormality of the ovulation cycle.

nodes.label: Abnormal chorioretinal morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the choroid and retina.

nodes.label: Abnormal dental enamel morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the dental enamel.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the costochondral junction
nodes.def: Any anomaly of the costochondral junction. The costochondral junctions are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum.

nodes.label: Thickened cortex of long bones
nodes.def: Abnormal thickening of the cortex of long bones.

nodes.label: Hypopigmentation of the skin
nodes.def: A reduction of skin color related to a decrease in melanin production and deposition.

nodes.label: Abnormal palmar dermatoglyphics
nodes.def: An abnormality of the dermatoglyphs, i.e., an abnormality of the patterns of ridges of the skin of palm of hand.

nodes.label: Abnormality of prenatal development or birth
nodes.def: An abnormality of the fetus or the birth of the fetus, excluding structural abnormalities.

nodes.label: Hypotonia
nodes.def: Hypotonia is an abnormally low muscle tone (the amount of tension or resistance to movement in a muscle). Even when relaxed, muscles have a continuous and passive partial contraction which provides some resistance to passive stretching. Hypotonia thus manifests as diminished resistance to passive stretching. Hypotonia is not the same as muscle weakness, although the two conditions can co-exist.

nodes.label: Flexion contracture
nodes.def: A flexion contracture is a bent (flexed) joint that cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement of joints.

nodes.label: Abnormal abdomen morphology
nodes.def: A structural abnormality of the abdomen ('belly'), that is, the part of the body between the pelvis and the thorax.

nodes.label: Abnormal rib cage morphology
nodes.def: A morphological anomaly of the rib cage.

nodes.label: Abnormal right ventricle morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the right ventricle of the heart.

nodes.label: Abnormal cardiac ventricle morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of a cardiac ventricle.

nodes.label: Double outlet right ventricle
nodes.def: Double outlet right ventricle (DORV) is a type of ventriculoarterial connection in which both great vessels arise entirely or predominantly from the right ventricle.

nodes.label: Short toe
nodes.def: A toe that appears disproportionately short compared to the foot.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the nose
nodes.def: An abnormality of the nose.

nodes.label: Conductive hearing impairment
nodes.def: An abnormality of vibrational conductance of sound to the inner ear leading to impairment of sensory perception of sound.

nodes.label: Recurrent respiratory infections
nodes.def: An increased susceptibility to respiratory infections as manifested by a history of recurrent respiratory infections.

nodes.label: Abnormal femoral neck morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

nodes.label: Abnormal femoral head morphology
nodes.def: An abnormality of the femoral head.

nodes.label: Atherosclerosis
nodes.def: A condition characterized by patchy atheromas or atherosclerotic plaques which develop in the walls of medium-sized and large arteries and can lead to arterial stenosis with reduced or blocked blood flow.

nodes.label: Skeletal dysplasia
nodes.def: A general term describing features characterized by abnormal development of bones and connective tissues.

nodes.label: Abnormal ulnar metaphysis morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the portion of the ulna between the epiphysis and the diaphysis.

nodes.label: Reduced circulating complement concentration
nodes.def: An immunodeficiency defined by the absent or suboptimal functioning of one of the complement system proteins.

nodes.label: Pituitary adenoma
nodes.def: A benign epithelial tumor derived from intrinsic cells of the adenohypophysis (anterior pituitary).

nodes.label: Vertebral fusion
nodes.def: A developmental defect leading to the union of two adjacent vertebrae.

nodes.label: Abnormal peripheral myelination
nodes.def: An abnormality of the myelination of motor and sensory peripheral nerves. These are axons for motor nerves and dendrites for sensory nerves in the strict anatomic sense.

nodes.label: Abnormality of the cervical spine
nodes.def: Any abnormality of the cervical vertebral column.

nodes.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving bones of the feet
Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the upper limbs
nodes.def: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the upper limbs.

nodes.label: Abnormal coronary artery morphology
nodes.def: Any structural abnormality of the coronary arteries.

nodes.label: Metacarpal synostosis
nodes.def: Fusion involving two or more metacarpal bones (A synostosis of the first metacarpal and the proximal phalanx of the thumb can also be observed, note that the first metacarpal bone corresponds to a proximal phalanx).
